<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'm glad to see a lot of great posts here.<P>You know, an extra three bucks a month won't kill us.  However, it's a trend we don't want to see continue.<P>Let's face it, they can't make everyone happy.  Even if they fixed a lot of problems, they would still have many people unhappy.<P>However.   There are outstanding issues that we all want to see resolved.   We want a new interface.   We want the Bazzar.   We want the normal day-to-day bugs corrected.   Get the horses working better, please.  Simply put:  Give us what you said you would.<P>This all can take time, sure.  But when we all see some new hype about a new expansion coming out, it infuriates us!  And we have every right to be angry.   Why the hell are you doing working on a new expansion, when all we want you to be working on now is fixing the outstanding issues?<P>The funny thing I see in many of these posts is how most people are willing to actually pay the extra 30%, and happily so, just to get the bugs fixed.  That's pretty bad.<P>They don't give us expansions, we pay for them.  The new features?  We PAY for them.  If you're increasing the rate because of the expansions costing you more money, then give the expansions away for free.<P>If anything, I'd like to see better customer service.  We are treated from the customer service end as parisites, always looking to screw them for items or whatever, and are given NO respect.   Hell, EQ costs as much as my ISP, and if I have a problem with that, I call them (free phone support?  Novel.), they believe what I am saying, and they don't tell me that I did something wrong or that they can't help me.  If I say I couldn't connect last week, they give me a week for free.   <P>Someone here mentioned "You show devotion to them, they show devotion to you"...   hehe yea okay.   In other words "If you sign a contract that you will pay us a whole bunch of money or we can sue you/wreck your credit/etc, and not have to do ANYTHING at all to keep you interested except the contract, we will give you a lower price."<P>Plus, nothing has been said from the SoE side about using the extra income for anything.  They did not say they were going to use the money to improve the game.  They want us to believe that they are FORCED to raise the rates; just to continue the way they have been.<P>Well I don't know.   I like Everquest.  It's fun for now, I can't wait to get my Magician Epic if I ever can (don't get me started on that one) and I'd like to see all the dragons take part in killing them.   <P>But, I'll get sick of it - because nothing changes, it's always broken in some way or another, and they don't deliver on their promises.<P>-CB
