<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Falcone:<BR><STRONG>well I read most of the posts here. Some good points, some are way off base. First the rate hike it self. I see many comments of "30% is not modest". First point is that , when looked at on an anual basis, the price hike is 10% not 30%. An increase is price for product in the range of 5 to 10% a year is pretty common across most retail or cust service industries. This is to cover both the raises they have given to their employees as well as the increased costs of raw materials which, in this case, would be serevers and computer parts( you dont think they havent put new Hard drives and CPUs in each of the server units do you?) as well as bandwith cost. Among the things that everyone seems to be getting wrong is That Mr Smedley talks of having a development team numbering 50 people. Many post here have misquoted this as saying Verant has 50 employees. Hello he was talking about the development team. There is also a maintenece staff for hardware and network upgrades and repairs. There is The CS staff. There is the sales staff. There is the producer staff. If the total number of all these people is under 200, I would be very surprised.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>You sound like a true blue VI/SOE staffer attempting to promote the year subscription rate.  Unfortunately, two things. 1) If someone does sign up for a year subscription rate, which costs less, they will not get that same rate the year after.  Because of this, their rate, and thus percent increase, will go up beyond 10% in total. 2) Because most of us are unhappy, you must be crazy to think we would sign up for a full year of the same subpar crap that we have dealt with for the past 3 years.  The monthly rate increase is a 30% increase, so that makes the rest of your comments about a 10% rate increase moot.  And I don't care how many employees are working for that company, I only care about them requiring more money to play the same old game (or lack thereof).<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><STRONG>As for those of you who have played this game since day one or at least since the days of early Kunark and state that VI has not upgraded or fixed anything, What the hell game have you been playing? Class penalties have been removed. Ui has been upgraded alot since velious. 2 new races, 2 new classes. contunued attempt to improve and upgrade and balance classes (this is on going inspite of the fact that VI has stated on numerous occasions that they would no longer look at class balancing). The latest round of improvements, especially the chat features are vast improvements to the game. Ally or raid channels has been on the top of the wish list for a long time. This also helps to alivieate the bazaar fiasco to an extent as now a global trade channel is at this very moment in use on you server. (on Karana the channel is trade: no password). I went through the EC tunnel and thought I was going LD cause I didn't see hardly anyone. It was empty or almost so. Existing zones have been upgraded and added. Someone posted that the old world zones should be upgraded like Blackburrow and Runneye. Ah well you might have had a chance of making a point if you didn't use as examples 2 zones that have been revamped. Kithicor forest, Blackburrow, Runneye, Befallen, Split paw lair, Cazic-thule, Lesser Faydark. These old world zones have all been revamped at one time or another since release ( did I miss any ?). 5 outer planes. Stonebrunt Mtns, The hole, and Paineel have all been added on zones to the Original EQ for free.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>You haven't been paying attention to our posts.  We have acknowledged getting upgrades, but that most upgrades came with expansions that we purchased.  Velious UI improvements?  Yup, came with Velious.  2 new races and classes?  Yup came with Kunark and SoL.  Continued class balance?  Ya, 3 years after the game's release VI finally gets around to caster balance... how nice.  Multiple chat channels?  Yes, something players have asked for forever, but only now included because a) other competitor games have done it, and b) as you said, help alleviate the bazaar fiasco.  Unfortunately, alternate chat channels was not a selling point for SoL - a new Bazaar WAS a selling point for SoL, and still has yet to be delivered. Thus blatant illegal false advertising.  Upgraded zones?  Some of which were disappointing, and some of which were almost a necessity (neriak).  So, in a couple of cases, is nice, but does not warrant a 30% rate increase.  Added new zones for free?  Again, would like to point out that the game was initially released short a few zones, so it sure was nice of them to make up for their downfall.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><STRONG>Another thing I hear people gripe about is the CS. I have played since 5 months after release and have never had a problem getting my problem addressed in a timley professional or curtios manner. Maybe you think you can do better. Id like to see the hands of all the people who have had to provide CS to 100000 customers at once? Thats what I thought, very few of you.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>We are not talking about you or the minority who may have had "nothing but good" CS experience (no matter how much I don't believe that comment anyway).  We are talking about the majority of us who have had many bad experiences.  I could care less if I could do better at CS - that is besides the point.  The point is that they have cruddy CS service, which is acknowledged by the majority of the player base.  So cruddy, in fact, that again, a 30% rate increase is not warranted.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><STRONG>Does this mean the game is perfect. Of course not. Show me a game that is. Show me a game that has up to 100000 people all accessing the servers over the internet and playing a RT game of this magnitude that doesnt have problems. Oh wait, there arnt any other games that even qualify . Why? Because in spite of the problems, and yes Im as disappointed as anyone with them, This is by far, the best interactive RT MMORPG out there.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I don't care if there are any other games that have come out that can truly compete with EQ.  EQ is still full of shotty programming and the companies are constantly making bad decisions.  Again, just because no real competition has come out for this game (although some might disagree with me) does not warrant a 30% rate increase.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><STRONG>One last point that I dont think anyone has raised. Whether you like it or not, VI is developing other games most notably SWG. This cost money. These games, while in development, are not generating revenue. art of the increase in the EQ subs rate is to pay for this development. Some of you may feel this is wrong but there isnt a succesful gaming company out there that doesnt take a percentage of their income and put it towards development of future product. The cost of Beta servers for SWG are also a very real cost that part of this increase goes to play for. The good news is that once SWG goes live, it will be more self supporting and my guess is that you will be able o do a dual subscription that will keep you near the same cost for EQ ( much like the long term plans for the current rate hike ).</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Wrong.  Many game companies do take the proceeds from game A to help develop game B, but I WILL NOT pay extra money for EQ so they can further develop a non-EQ related game, one which I will never play.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><STRONG>In short costs do rise and a 10% annual increase is not that out of line. You can say what you like about bugs and incomplete items but this is the best game on the internet period, thats why we all play.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Actually, in short a 30% rate increase is very out of line.  This is the ONLY real game out there on the market, but even still, it is far from great.  And that is why I am cancelling my account.
