Here is what i would like to see.  EQ has scheduled patches, and scheduled down time.  That is fine, the game needs patches, and maybe it can't be patched as easilly while it's up and running.  But for every scheduled patch, there are 2 or more EMERGANCY patches, or unscheduled patches, and login server failures.  EQ should reimburse us for UNSCHEDULED down time.  If your ISP goes down, you can get reimbursed for the down time.  Good hosting services will automatically refund you for their downtime, and will tell you exactly how much down time they had that wasn't scheduled. I don't agree with their reasoning behind raising the prices, i've also read many of the posts (not all, 4 pages is a lot) and agree with a lot of the points.  Unfortunately no matter how much we complain, the price change will happen.  The least they could do is refund us for the down time they experience.  How many people got refunds for when SoL shut down the servers for days at a time?  I didn't.  <P>Cantril Ivoryshield<BR>51 Cleric of Bristlebane<BR>Sularus Oth Mithas<BR>Mith Marr
