I don't believe that the rate increase is unreasonable.  For those that do it is a very simple matter of cancelling your account.  What about all the time you have already invested in it?  That is up to you.  This is a source of entertainment not an investment.  You will never reap anything from this service but entertainment.  If you die tomorrow your family will receive nothing from it.  If you have invested your time in this game then it is because you wanted too for the entertainment value.  I read a post that said you'd like a detailed accounting of why the increase.  I don't know about your job experience, but I've never worked for a company that would do this and it is a ridiculous notion.  VI is providing a service for a cost.  Either you feel the service is worth it and pay or you don't.  I have been very frustrated at time with the tech support, bugs, lack of content, and everything else.  I still choose to play though because overall I like the game and enjoy playing it.  If I didn't then I would cancel today and find something else to ammuse myself.  My biggest gripe with VI/SOE right now is the fact that Luclin was sold as having several improvements that still do not exist.  This is a real case of not getting what you pay for.  You can all flame me for being an idiot, but this is my choice and I don't ask you to like it.<P>--------------------<P>Tanvarien Panteras<BR>33rd Level Ranger<BR>Elite Guards of Norrath
