Greetings all.  <BR>This is incredible.  I'll start off with the statement and fact that a $3 increase in cost per month indicates that these people have no concept of the word "TACT".  <P>I own 4, count'em 4 EQ accounts and I have three computers networked together and three of the accounts are online at the same time.  That's $12/month more that I have to pay now for a grand total of $51.80/month. Ok so I don't really need cable T.V. if i'm playing EQ.  But seriously, I don't understand why such a huge increase in cost has occurred here.  This is a 30% increase.  Will my 51 Wizzie get a 30% increase in the damage he can do now?  Or 30% increase in my mana regen ability?  no.  Of course not.  The best logical question is ...will i get a 30% increase in service?  I have had several times where I petition and get no response at all.  I petition again and find that my petition is still in the que after HOURS of waiting.  I send in a bug report and don't even so much as get a response that they have received the info that I'm volunteering to them...free of charge...in order to increase the quality of software that I'm PAYING to use already.  <P>The tactful thing to do here, would have been to raise the cost from $9.95/month to $10.95/month  then after 6 months or a year, go to $11.95/month and so on till they got to $12.95.  Obviously somebody woke up and suddenly realized they have not been charging us enough and oh since "...we have not increased the cost for the last 3 years..." we are going to make up for lost time!  Is that the way you KEEP a loyal customer base?  I don't think so.  Yeah, for entertainment value $12.95/month is nothing.  Movies, Ice Skating, Dirt Biking, water skiing...it all costs money and usually much more than $12.95 for a whole month of fun.  Even a good paper back book costs $7.95 or more (new off the shelf).  But with those things, quality of customer service is not part of the package.  <P>Oh yeah, I forgot that on top of all this, you have to PAY $50 per character to have it moved from one account to another on the same server.  If you request to switch servers...not only do you have to pay, you LOOSE all your stuff!!!!  Yes, and especially your quested items that are NO DROP...that can not in any way affect the server's economy.  All that time you spent camping PoF and you finally won the roll...all for nothing.<P>My worry i suppose, is that next month or next year, will they decide to raise the mark another $3.00???  I don't care if i've played since I first started and I have 10 level 60 chars, I'll be finding a place that doesn't have this idea that they haven't been charging enough so it's time to make up for lost time/money without SUBSTANTIALLY increasing their services.<P>There are those who probably think i'm a whinning baby.  Well, friend, I paid enough per month BEFORE the increased monthly charge to have the right to be a whinning baby.  So until you are willing to donate to my cause, you can take a hike.<P>Sincerely Thayland
