Ok, ladies and gents...here comes my 2cp...<P>This is a problem, this extra $3.06 a month is rediculous.  The reasons listed for the increase do not justify the increase.  For the past three years EQ has been running on their current budget of $9.89/mo./user.  This being a huge number, ought to cover their expenses for everquest.  Granted its a HUGE game, its by far no nearly the best game.   Don't get me wrong.  I love the game, I'm hooked.  However, most of the time I can't stand looking at the screen.  I'm very into the eye candy, I want beautiful mountains, mist, flowing water...and believe me my computer can handle it.  And I know most everyone who plays EQ has a computer that can handle not the top-notch graphics, but better looking things then what we see...not blocks on blocks.  Thats gripe number one.  <P>I haven't gotten a real chance to run into too many bugs.  I know they exist, I don't get to play just like every one else when they're fixing a problem caused by a fix to another problem cause by a fix....etc etc etc.  Thats bad...but not the worse I've seen.  There are some games out there that continously get pathched, network code constantly changed because people are hacking it, or there are holes here and there for this and that.  All I can say is, I haven't run into any.  Nobody has hacked my account, I've never seen anybody cheat, kudos for that.  So, to everyone who complains about patches...if you don't want the patches stop complaining about the game.  The patches will stop   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> Second gripe...<P>Back onto the money thing...ok...here in the US, we look at an average of 3% inflation each year.  That means the cost of living, advertising, salaries, everything and anything you could ever put on an EQ bill...on average...increases about 3% a year.  So, knowing that lets take the original cost of EQ, which I pay $9.89 per month.  Multiply that time 1.03 and you get how much it would cost, or actually how much it should cost to play EQ based on the original price.  Do that multiplication 2 times more and you'll come to the number inflation has dictated for the price of EQ monthly.  My calcs show thats rougly $10.81/mo./user american dollars.  Lets see here, WHERE IS ALL THE OTHER MONEY GOING YOU DOLTS!!!<P>I like one post I saw, I think whoever thought 30% increase is ok should get their @$$ down to my office and tell my boss that I need a 30% increase, and don't tell me I didn't work for it...<P>Utilieas<BR>26 Mage<BR>Brell<P>--------------------<P>----------------------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160671" TARGET=_blank>Luman</A>, 17 Cleric, Brell<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160662" TARGET=_blank>Utilieas</A>, 26 mage, Brell
