Perhaps there is some misunderstanding here.  Verant/SOE indeed DO need to work on what they ALREADY HAVE before jumping into new expansions.  Every new expansion it has been exactly the same story:<P><B>VI</B>: "Hey look!  We're making a new expansion called Ruins of Kunark.  It will increase content by 30%.  There will be zones for people of all levels... And just LOOK at all the new stuff!  The Iksar are a new playable race!"<BR><B>Customer</B>: "But for the last year people have been screaming at you to fix xxx bug and balance all the classes.  If you release new content, is there a snowball's chance in hell you'll have ANYONE working on that old stuff, or are they all going to be working on fixing the bugs you released with your new expansion?  Do you even HAVE a CS department?"<P>1 Year Later======<BR><B>Verant/SOE</B>: "Look!  We're releasing a new expansion called Scars of Velious.  It will increase world size by 30%!  And even though no players level 34 or below can go there without getting their @$$ handed to them by, of all things, a snow bunny, the players above level 35 have all sorts of pHaT l3wT to explore.  No, there are no new playable races, but we added two new Planes..."<BR><B>Irate Customer</B>: "You still haven't fixed all that old stuff... and are you ever going to balance the classes?  Necro pets are still ripping everything in the zone to shreds.  Do you even HAVE a CS department?"<P>1 Year Later=======<BR><B>VI/SOE</B>: "Now do we have an expansion for you!  It's called Shadows of Luclin!  We're completely overhauling everything and adding a new race AND new class.  And just look at all the new content!  I bet that's at LEAST 30% of the old world... right?"<BR><B>Customer</B>: "Okay, I see you've been working on, err... balancing the classes... sort of, I guess... but why does it take me 5 minutes to zone, even before I buy the expansion... and hey all my buffs suddenly disappeared?  Why is the Bazaar not implemented?  Why are there missing mobs in the dungeons?  It still costs 300kpp to get 250 tailoring... and my guild could get better loot, much cheaper, and much faster, from sacking ToV and ST... and why do half of the new models look like cheesy comic book cliches?  At least Alternative Advancement is kinda cool.  But... You're never going to get a CS department, are you? Are you even listening to me?"<BR><B>SOE/VI</B>: "Looook into my eyes... you want to spend 30% more for EQ..."<P>Two months later=========<BR><B>verant/SONY ONLINE ENTERTAINASTRAVAGANZA</B>: "Sony's marketing division tells us that an obscure poll tells us that you want to pay $50 a month to be treated special.  So her's what we're gonig to do:  We're going to release a new Legends server set, where we actuially pay attention to you (you have the money ON you, right?) and you get a real CS department and your own shiny special website.  Oh, you'll have to leave friends on the older servers, but you don't want any part of those poor bastards whom we've been suckering all along, do you?  Come here little boy, you'll get treated like a REAL gamer here... heheheh..."<BR><B>Consumer 83.b</B>: "How stupid do you think I am?"<P>Today========<BR><B>SONY, HEGEMONY OF EARTH</B>: "Hey check it out!  Planes of Power! THIS time there's new content for newbies... like.. um, the Plane of Knowledge.  Yeah... newbies will just... hmm.  Well our uber level 60 players get 19 other Planes to harvest pHaT l3wT from."<BR><B>a_hapless_peon_01</B>: "Yes master... anything for a gnomish paladin..."<P>====Note to the Crack Dealers====<BR>I offer up my money in loving sacrifice for you, oh Grand Exalted Master.  Please do not raise bandwidth.  Please open up a more expensive booth at next year's E3, which I won't be at.  Please do not fix old bugs, but continue to release "new content" with even more bugs than before.  Network code is too much of a hassle to fix.  Just reward me with pHaT l3wt when I hit level 60 and all will be well.  Please do not fix t