And one more note: Sony does not buy 405 new computers a year  They just don't.  I know this because every expansion they release ever-more clogged network code.  That is one reason it takes 5 minutes to zone.  That issue is not a bug, not a new feature, it is a result of overclogged code, even when your computer doesn't HAVE the expansion and is thus incapable of using the new expansion structure.<P>They couldn't afford to replace those computers even if they wanted to, and when exactly would this switching occur?  You can't just recopy all that data from the old server 'puters onto new ones.  Since MMOG's are PERSISTENT, there's no tiem for this, and don't think they can recopy that volume of information while a server goes down for 2 hours.  In short, VI/SOE doesn't replace those nifty $10g computers.  They simply make new Legends servers with those nifty new 'puters.  K?<P>I mean, have you ever heard a patch say, 'We were just going to upgrade the computers so we can handle the load/new content?'  Come on now, don't lie to yourselves...  those =obsolete= computers have housed your characters from creation to current day.<P>--------------------<P>That's just the way it is...
